HEADWORD: Thewed
<hw>Thewed</hw> <pr>(th⟦umac⟧d)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Furnished with thews or muscles; <as>as, a well-<ex>thewed</ex>
limb</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Accustomed; mannered.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>John Skelton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Yet would not seem so rude and <qex>thewed</qex> ill.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

